# ButtonLink Component Rules

## Overview
Rules for `src/components/atoms/ButtonLink.tsx`

## Purpose
Atom for a link styled as a button with brand-consistent variants.

## Rules
- ✅ Props: `href` (required), `children` (required), `variant?` ("primary" | "outline"), `className?`.
- ✅ Styling: Base `inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded transition-colors`.
- ✅ Variants:
  - primary: `bg-[#8a0028] text-white hover:opacity-90`
  - outline: `border border-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-900 hover:text-white`
- ✅ Export both named and default.
- ✅ Accessibility: Uses Next.js `Link` with text label.

## Template
```typescript
export type ButtonLinkProps = {
  href: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
  variant?: "primary" | "outline";
  className?: string;
};
```

## Usage
```tsx
<ButtonLink href="/catering">Find out more</ButtonLink>
<ButtonLink href="/order" variant="primary">Order now</ButtonLink>
```

## QA Checklist
- Correct variant classes applied.
- Hover/focus visible.
- Accepts custom `className` for spacing when composed.